# Files excluded from the WordPress.org SVN deploy (10up action reads .distignore).
# Mirrors .gitattributes export-ignore, which governs the git-archive release zip.
#
# /.git is NOT optional, and it is NOT redundant with .gitattributes. The mere
# presence of this file makes 10up's deploy.sh take a different code path:
#
#   .distignore present -> rsync -rc --exclude-from=.distignore $GITHUB_WORKSPACE/ trunk/
#   .distignore absent  -> git archive HEAD | tar x
#
# The rsync path copies the raw actions/checkout workspace, where .git is an
# ordinary directory that nothing excludes for free — git-archive is what made
# the exclusion implicit, and we are not on that path. Without this line the
# entire repository history is committed to the WordPress.org SVN trunk and
# shipped inside every zip users download from wordpress.org.
#
# Do not "simplify" this by deleting .distignore to fall back to git archive:
# deploy-wordpress-org.yml injects the version with sed into the WORKING TREE and
# never commits it, so `git archive HEAD` would publish an unpatched Version: and
# Stable tag. The rsync path is load-bearing.
/.git
/.github
/.wordpress-org
/.claude
/tests
/vendor
/phpstan
/languages/*.po
/.gitattributes
/.gitignore
/.distignore
/.phase1
/.phpunit.cache
/composer.json
/composer.lock
/phpunit.xml
/phpstan.neon
/pint.json
/CHANGELOG.md
/README.md
/CLAUDE.md
/graphify-out
